Choices can use `is` and `is not` when their payloads are equality-safe.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    first = Status::Ready
    second = Status::Ready

    same = first is second
]

Two choice values are equal when they use the same variant and their payload
values are equal.

A choice with a collection, struct or another unsupported payload cannot use
structural equality. Pattern matching still works.
